1️⃣ Check Apache Configuration for Zabbix
The package zabbix-apache-conf provides a configuration file for Apache. Usually located at:
/etc/apache2/conf-available/zabbix.conf

Check its contents:
cat /etc/apache2/conf-available/zabbix.conf
You should see something like:

Alias /zabbix /usr/share/zabbix

<Directory "/usr/share/zabbix">
    Options FollowSymLinks
    AllowOverride None
    Require all granted
</Directory>

<Directory "/usr/share/zabbix/conf">
    Require all denied
</Directory>


Make sure the config is enabled:

sudo a2enconf zabbix
sudo systemctl reload apache2

2️⃣ Check PHP Version and Modules

Zabbix 7.4.5 requires PHP 8.x (or PHP 7.4+ depending on your OS). To check the PHP CLI version:
php -v

Then check installed PHP modules required for Zabbix:

php -m | grep -E 'mysqli|pdo_mysql|bcmath|ctype|curl|gd|mbstring|xml|json'


Required modules include: mysqli, pdo_mysql, bcmath, curl, mbstring, xml, gd, json.

3️⃣ Check Zabbix Frontend PHP Configuration

The PHP frontend config file is located at:

/etc/zabbix/web/zabbix.conf.php


Important settings to check:

$DB['TYPE']     = 'MYSQL';
$DB['SERVER']   = 'localhost';
$DB['PORT']     = '0';
$DB['DATABASE'] = 'zabbix';
$DB['USER']     = 'zabbix';
$DB['PASSWORD'] = 'your_password';

$ZBX_SERVER      = '127.0.0.1';
$ZBX_SERVER_PORT = '10051';


$ZBX_SERVER must point to the running Zabbix server.

Database credentials must match what’s in MySQL.

4️⃣ Check Apache & PHP Logs

Check for errors that could prevent report generation:

sudo tail -n 50 /var/log/apache2/error.log
sudo tail -n 50 /var/log/zabbix/zabbix_web_service.log


Common issues:
PHP timeout too low for report generation
Missing PHP modules (gd for graphs)
Wrong $ZBX_SERVER IP/port

5️⃣ Verify Frontend Access
Open the Zabbix frontend:
http://<server-ip>/zabbix


Go to: Administration → Test → Report generating test
If it fails, check the web service logs (/var/log/zabbix/zabbix_web_service.log) for the exact reason.

✅ Summary

Apache serves PHP frontend (zabbix-frontend-php)
PHP must have all required modules installed
Zabbix Web Service must be running and reachable by PHP (127.0.0.1:10051)

Database credentials must match

cat /etc/apache2/conf-available/zabbix.conf
# Define /zabbix alias, this is the default
<IfModule mod_alias.c>
    Alias /zabbix /usr/share/zabbix/ui
</IfModule>

<Directory "/usr/share/zabbix/ui">
    Options FollowSymLinks
    AllowOverride None
    Order allow,deny
    Allow from all

    <IfModule mod_php.c>
        php_value max_execution_time 300
        php_value memory_limit 128M
        php_value post_max_size 16M
        php_value upload_max_filesize 2M
        php_value max_input_time 300
        php_value max_input_vars 10000
        php_value always_populate_raw_post_data -1
    </IfModule>

    <IfModule mod_php7.c>
        php_value max_execution_time 300
        php_value memory_limit 128M
        php_value post_max_size 16M
        php_value upload_max_filesize 2M
        php_value max_input_time 300
        php_value max_input_vars 10000
        php_value always_populate_raw_post_data -1
    </IfModule>
</Directory>

<Directory "/usr/share/zabbix/ui/conf">
    Order deny,allow
    Deny from all
    <files *.php>
        Order deny,allow
        Deny from all
    </files>
</Directory>

<Directory "/usr/share/zabbix/ui/app">
    Order deny,allow
    Deny from all
    <files *.php>
        Order deny,allow
        Deny from all
    </files>
</Directory>

<Directory "/usr/share/zabbix/ui/include">
    Order deny,allow
    Deny from all
    <files *.php>
        Order deny,allow
        Deny from all
    </files>
</Directory>

<Directory "/usr/share/zabbix/ui/local">
    Order deny,allow
    Deny from all
    <files *.php>
        Order deny,allow
        Deny from all
    </files>
</Directory>

<Directory "/usr/share/zabbix/ui/vendor">
    Order deny,allow
    Deny from all
    <files *.php>
        Order deny,allow
        Deny from all
    </files>
</Directory>
